Program: The Forum
Title: Us and Them
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p017cr7r
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 29 Apr 2013
Is it helpful to view the world as being divided along fault-lines of gender, class, race or religion? Matthew Taylor talks to anthropologist Laura Nader, who says we need to find new dialogues between the West and the Middle East that recognise our common humanity; historian David Cannadine who says that as well as studying conflict, we should explore our undivided past; and novelist Aminatta Forna, who examines the aftermath of civil war through her fiction; what about when 'them' also means 'us'? Image: Children playing tug-of-war, Credit: Jens-Ulrich Koch/AFP/Getty Images Show less